<synopsis><code mime="text/x-python">
@returns(none)
def remove_all_children()
</code></synopsis>
<p>Removes all children of @self.</p><p>This function releases the reference added by inserting a child actor
in the list of children of @self.</p><p>If the reference count of a child drops to zero, the child will be
destroyed. If you want to ensure the destruction of all the children
of @self, use clutter_actor_destroy_all_children().</p>

